The Narrative: The New Hunger
(Read Aloud)
"The Thirst for blood, Molag Bal's primal curse, is a dull, distant ache, easily ignored. The hunger for flesh, Namira's raw gift, is sated from your earlier meal. But a third, more insidious craving has taken root in the pit of your stomach since you created your ghoul. It is a nauseating, compelling desire for things that are not just dead, but wrong. For the complex, pungent aroma of decay. For the delicate texture of infection. Peryite's influence has altered your palate."
"You try to keep up appearances. You pick up a strip of dried venison, a staple of mortal survival. The moment it nears your face, your stomach churns. It smells like nothing. A sterile, uninteresting piece of matter. There is no life in it, but more importantly, there is no process in it. No decay. No disease. It is an empty calorie, and your new body has no use for it."
The Temptation: The Perfect Morsel
(Read Aloud)
"Then, the breeze shifts."
"You smell something exquisite. It is a complex bouquet that makes your mouth flood with saliva. It has a base note of hot, living blood and the salt of sweat, overlaid with the sharp, tangy, almost cheesy aroma of burgeoning infection. It is the most delicious thing you have ever smelled."
"Your eyes are drawn to its source: Old BjornΓÇÖs horse, Mable. She is standing by the cart, stamping her hoof nervously. On her flank, where the harness has rubbed the skin away, is a small, raw sore. A single drop of blood and clear, yellowish fluid weeps from the wound, glistening in the firelight."
"To your new senses, that sore is not a wound; it is a delicacy. It is a perfectly balanced amuse-bouche of life and decay. The urge to press your tongue against the raw, infected meat is an overwhelming, physical craving. You know, with absolute certainty, that tasting it would be euphoric."
The Complication: The First Minion
(Read Aloud)
"As you grapple with this disgusting new appetite, a low, wet growl echoes from the shadows of the ruined inn where you hid your creation. The Plague Ghoul is hungry. You can feel its mindless craving through your psychic link, a dull, repetitive thudding against your consciousness: Feed. Feed. Feed."
"You now have two immediate, pressing hungers to manage: your own monstrous new craving, and the needs of the monster you created. The ghoul is a loose variable. If it gets too hungry, it might wander into the refugee camp, exposing the party. You must deal with it."

The Intervention: The Master's Critique
(This scene is triggered while Alfonso is grappling with his new hunger for the horse's infected sore and the distraction of his hidden, hungry ghoul.)
(Read Aloud)
"Before you can decide which fire to put out first, a flicker of movement by the campfire catches your eye. A single, black raven has landed silently on a log near your pack. It is unnaturally still, its obsidian eyes fixed on you with an unblinking, intelligent gaze. It is a creature out of place in the smoky, chaotic ruins."
"The raven hops forward, drops a small, rolled scroll sealed with dark wax at your feet, gives a single, soft caw that sounds less like a bird and more like a sigh of disappointment, and then takes flight, vanishing into the night."
"The scroll is made of thick, expensive vellum. The wax seal is impressed with the familiar, jagged crest of the Volskygge clan. You break the seal. The note inside is written in ValeriusΓÇÖs jagged, elegant script."
The Note:
"I observed your... meal... in the ruins. Your methods are dangerously crude. We are not feral ghouls scrabbling in the dirt; we are the lords of this new age."
