"You are an investment, Alfonso. Do not become a liability."
ΓÇö V.C.
The Realization:
(Read Aloud)
"The note is not just a command; it is an act of profound intimidation. He was here. Or one of his agents was. He watched you feed on the cultist. He knows about your ghoul. He has access to your camp, close enough to leave a physical object at your feet without anyone noticing."
"The message is an ultimatum, layered with contempt. He is disgusted by your methods, viewing your embrace of Namira's and Peryite's gifts as filthy and undisciplined. He is not offering guidance or tools. He is giving you a direct order to clean up your mess. He has judged your first act as his fledgling, and he has found it wanting."
The Choice: The Taskmaster's Burden
(Read Aloud)
"The pieces are all on the board. The vellum note in your hand feels heavier than stone, its elegant script a stark and damning judgment from the shadows. Valerius's ultimatum echoes in your mind: 'Silence it. Do not become a liability.'"
"At the same time, your own body betrays you. The intoxicating, complex aroma of the infected sore on Mable's flank continues to pull at your senses, a primal craving for the perfect, grotesque meal promised by your new patrons, Namira and Peryite. It is a siren song of euphoric indulgence."
"And from the darkness of the ruined inn, you feel the persistent, mindless thrum of your creation's hunger, a logistical problem that will not solve itself and threatens to expose you with every passing moment of inaction."
"You are caught between the cold, aristocratic demands of the vampire lord who sees you as a flawed tool, the disgusting new appetites of the Daedric Princes who see you as their burgeoning champion, and the immediate, practical needs of the monster you created. Your every instinct is being pulled in a different direction. You must now choose which demand to answer."

1. Obey the Master (An Act of Compliance): "Do you prioritize Valerius's command? Do you ignore your own ravenous hunger and slip away into the ruins to 'silence' your ghoul? This is the path of the pragmatist, the disciplined asset. You would be proving to Valerius that you can follow orders and control your creations, choosing his cold approval over the immediate satisfaction of your own debased appetites. You must decide if silencing the ghoul means destroying it, or merely feeding it to quiet it down for now."
2. Indulge the Self (An Act of Defiance): "Do you give in to your own primal craving? Do you ignore Valerius's judgment and the ghoul's hunger to pursue the exquisite new sensation offered by the horse's infected wound? This is now a direct act of rebellion against Valerius's philosophy, a declaration that you will embrace the filth he despises. It is the path of the true gourmand of rot, prioritizing personal indulgence above all else, even the commands of a powerful master."
3. Defy the Patrons (An Act of Revulsion): "Do you recoil from this entire monstrous reality? Do you ignore the horse, ignore Valerius's note, and march to the ruins with the singular purpose of destroying the ghoul you created? This is not an act of compliance to Valerius, but an act of self-hatred and defiance against Namira and Peryite. It is an attempt to reject the monstrous path you have started down, to undo your first act of creation, even if it means angering the very gods who are empowering you."
