4. Saijah: The Dying Breath
Context: You are sitting on a log, staring into the fire. You are seeking the rhythm of the GreenΓÇöthe heartbeat of KynarethΓÇöto calm your nerves after the unnatural horror of the dragon.
The Narrative:
"You close your eyes and reach out with your senses, hunting for the pulse of the land. You find only a scream.
The circle around this campfire feels like a collection of wounds in the fabric of the world. Your perception, heightened by the stress of the day, picks apart the specific nature of the rot sitting beside you.
To your right sits Alfonso. He radiates a sucking void, a hunger that actively consumes the light around him. He smells of wet earth, broken bone, and the sickly-sweet scent of fungus blooming on a corpse. You can feel the microorganisms in the soil beneath his boots dying, their life force drained simply by his proximity. He feels like a sinkhole, dragging everything near him into a pit of digestion and decay.
